        <m_lines m_style="Text" m_yOffset="5" m_string="Lara anti-thanks the fact that all of the credit columns are permanantly center-justified and had to be aligned manually. Yeah you read that right. I manually added spaces to everything to make it look like normal credits. It looked reeeeaaally bad otherwise, man! It was totally unreadable!! So if you looked at this game's credits and went ''yeah these are just, your completely average regular credits'' that was me. But just that part, I didn't code the stuff that makes it scroll. Oh, while I'm chattin' up a storm, did you find my easter egg? My actual easter egg, not this!"/>
        <m_lines m_style="Text" m_yOffset="5" m_string="It's somewhere out in the world of OUTER WILDS..." />
